Author: artem.pikulin#0794
Content: @jansako Hi! `Didn't receive any data since...` messages are related to Electrum server connections. It means that no data was received from particular Electrum server for 60 seconds so connection is forcefully aborted and reconnected then. It might mean that you have some connectivity issues on your server or maybe there's a problem with Electrum server itself. These messages can appear when no swaps are running as connections are kept active at background continously if coin is activated.

Author: artem.pikulin#0794
Content: If you see these messages often and have failed swaps please make sure that network connectivity on your node is in good state. If it's good but you still see this please submit an issue with logs to AtomicDEX-API repo: https://github.com/KomodoPlatform/atomicDEX-API/issues

Content: Will keep an eye on it, thank you!
